00:58.591 --> 01:00.459
<i>Heaven or hell?</i>

01:00.461 --> 01:04.263
<i>People don't find out where
they're headed until they die.</i>

01:04.265 --> 01:08.434
<i>But I know. I know
where everyone's going.</i>

01:08.436 --> 01:10.769
<i>Because I'm the one
who makes the decision.</i>

01:13.441 --> 01:16.975
<i>This was the moment
my life changed forever.</i>

01:16.977 --> 01:19.545
<i>Because God starting
speaking to me.</i>

01:35.662 --> 01:37.429
<i>He gave me a job.</i>

01:37.431 --> 01:40.165
<i>My purpose in life.</i>

01:40.167 --> 01:42.367
<i>The judgements.</i>

01:45.773 --> 01:47.306
<i>He told me as long as
I trusted my instincts</i>

01:47.308 --> 01:50.676
<i>and did my job...</i>

01:50.678 --> 01:51.878
<i>everything would be alright.</i>

03:02.115 --> 03:05.117
<i>My name is
Walter Gary Benjamin.</i>

03:05.119 --> 03:08.253
<i>My friends call me Wally.</i>

03:08.255 --> 03:10.088
<i>My enemies call me
"kid" or "dumbass"</i>

03:10.090 --> 03:13.258
<i>or sometimes "stupid fuck."</i>

03:13.260 --> 03:15.160
<i>My mom has always
gone with Walt,</i>

03:15.162 --> 03:18.297
<i>and my dad, whenever I talk
to him, goes with Walter.</i>

03:18.299 --> 03:21.900
<i>He's God, by the way.
My dad.</i>

03:21.902 --> 03:24.603
<i>And no, I'm not Jesus,
that was someone else.</i>

03:24.605 --> 03:25.971
<i>With a beard.</i>

03:40.287 --> 03:41.720
Eggs?

03:41.722 --> 03:43.222
I have to go to work.

03:43.224 --> 03:45.257
It's an important part of life,
you know, eating.

03:45.259 --> 03:47.025
I'm sorry, but being late
is not an option.

03:47.027 --> 03:48.493
You're never late.

03:48.495 --> 03:51.163
Because I always leave
at the same time. Goodbye.

03:51.165 --> 03:53.532
Well, what if you starve
to death on the way to work?

03:53.534 --> 03:55.701
I won't.
You might!

03:55.703 --> 03:56.703
I won't.

03:56.704 --> 03:58.036
Your bus could crash.

03:58.038 --> 04:01.173
Everybody dies on impact,
except you.

04:01.175 --> 04:02.841
But the paramedics
can't get to you,

04:02.843 --> 04:03.875
because you're trapped,

04:03.877 --> 04:05.611
under all the twisted metal,

04:05.613 --> 04:07.012
and the other dead passengers,

04:07.014 --> 04:09.047
and then there's gas,
all over the road!

04:09.049 --> 04:11.416
Now it doesn't explode,
which is a good thing.

04:11.418 --> 04:13.018
But while they're
busy making

04:13.020 --> 04:15.020
all of their explosion
preparations,

04:15.022 --> 04:18.123
who dies of starvation?

04:18.125 --> 04:20.459
You do!

04:56.096 --> 04:58.196
<i>Being who I am
isn't always easy.</i>

04:58.198 --> 04:59.865
<i>The job of deciding
someone's eternal fate</i>

04:59.867 --> 05:02.167
<i>is a great responsibility.</i>

05:22.089 --> 05:25.724
<i>Him, hell.
Her, heaven.</i>

05:25.726 --> 05:26.992
<i>Heaven.</i>

05:26.994 --> 05:31.797
<i>Heaven, hell.
Heaven.</i>

05:31.799 --> 05:33.031
<i>Heaven.</i>

05:33.033 --> 05:34.533
<i>When making a judgement,</i>

05:34.535 --> 05:36.575
<i>I'm required to look
past the obvious.</i>

05:43.444 --> 05:48.246
<i>Heaven. Heaven. Heaven.</i>

05:59.826 --> 06:03.528
<i>Most of the time, I'm able to
do my job without question.</i>

06:03.530 --> 06:05.931
<i>But it's hard for me on
this particular city bus.</i>

06:08.334 --> 06:10.902
<i>When I was eleven, I took this
same bus to the hospital</i>

06:10.904 --> 06:14.706
<i>with Jim a lot.</i>

06:14.708 --> 06:16.375
<i>He told me if he could
fight fires for a living,</i>

06:16.377 --> 06:17.909
<i>a little disease was
nothing to worry about.</i>

06:17.911 --> 06:19.311
Then everything's
gonna be okay?

06:19.313 --> 06:21.346
Then everything's gonna be okay.

06:29.323 --> 06:31.803
Dad, when I grow up,
I'm gonna be...

06:58.485 --> 07:01.353
Look at this kid,
all eager and shit.

07:01.355 --> 07:03.588
I take the time out of
my day to address

07:03.590 --> 07:04.823
your quirky little dumbass self,

07:04.825 --> 07:05.957
and you're just
gonna blow me off?

07:05.959 --> 07:07.259
I'm working, Vince.

07:07.261 --> 07:08.894
No, you're vacuuming.
I'm working.

07:08.896 --> 07:11.329
Constantly. See, I got this call
back on this jack-in-the-box

07:11.331 --> 07:12.764
spot they're shooting
up in Chi-town.

07:12.766 --> 07:14.499
Corey gave each of us a list
of pre-matinee duties

07:14.501 --> 07:16.268
that we're supposed to...
Corey gave up on life

07:16.270 --> 07:18.036
when he gained 40 pounds,
opted against using Rogaine

07:18.038 --> 07:20.005
and decided to manage
a fuckin' movie theatre

07:20.007 --> 07:21.473
was an acceptable
career choice.

07:21.475 --> 07:23.442
He's still our boss.
No, he's your boss.

07:23.444 --> 07:25.210
My boss is Brando.

07:25.212 --> 07:27.546
My boss is
motherfucking Denzel.

07:27.548 --> 07:29.414
My... my boss is that guy
who played Gandhi

07:29.416 --> 07:32.150
in that old-ass <i> Gandhi</i> movie.
Corey ain't shit.

07:32.152 --> 07:34.553
What was that?

07:34.555 --> 07:37.222
Ha! You know, I saw you
creeping up my perphery.

07:37.224 --> 07:38.557
You like what I was doing there?

07:38.559 --> 07:41.460
I was like, you know,
"Corey ain't shit!",

07:41.462 --> 07:43.695
knowing the whole time
you were coming right up on me.

07:43.697 --> 07:45.030
That's funny!

07:45.032 --> 07:47.532
Theatre 3 has puke
in one of the aisles,

07:47.534 --> 07:49.468
just for you, Vince.

07:49.470 --> 07:52.237
Yeah. Yeah, my boy,
he's all over that.

07:52.239 --> 07:54.239
Usually, when someone
identifies you by name,

07:54.241 --> 07:55.874
they're talking to you.

07:55.876 --> 07:58.396
Unless you've changed
your name to Douchebag.

08:07.688 --> 08:08.887
Lobby looks good.

08:08.889 --> 08:10.555
Thank you.

08:10.557 --> 08:12.524
The lobby floor is highest on
my list of pre-matinee duties,

08:12.526 --> 08:15.093
so I always make sure to...
Jesus Christ.

08:39.885 --> 08:42.486
- Undigested Milk Duds.
- Look at 'em.

08:42.489 --> 08:43.455
No thank you.

08:43.457 --> 08:45.023
Just fuckin' look at 'em!

08:45.025 --> 08:46.825
You're seein' general human
condition bullshit

08:46.827 --> 08:48.293
going on right in there, man!

08:48.295 --> 08:50.929
It's just a metaphor for life,
stupid fuck!

08:56.503 --> 08:58.803
<i>That's Kendall.</i>

08:58.805 --> 09:00.639
<i>Definitely heaven.</i>

09:00.641 --> 09:02.707
<i>I've liked her since the moment
she started working here,</i>

09:02.709 --> 09:04.976
<i>but she's Concessions.
I'm Tickets.</i>

09:04.978 --> 09:06.511
Yo, Kendall!

09:06.513 --> 09:08.673
<i>If only I can figure out
how to talk to her.</i>

09:13.319 --> 09:14.519
It's about time, Wally...

09:14.521 --> 09:16.354
<i>She says, cueing the music.</i>

09:18.425 --> 09:20.859
She says something
cool, poetic.

09:20.861 --> 09:22.427
Something cool,

09:22.429 --> 09:23.361
poetic.

09:23.363 --> 09:24.996
<i>I respond with equally profound</i>

09:24.998 --> 09:26.831
<i>yet effortless banter.</i>

09:26.833 --> 09:29.334
Words, words, words.

09:41.847 --> 09:43.081
I love you.

09:43.083 --> 09:44.449
You're staring.

09:44.451 --> 09:45.383
What?

09:45.385 --> 09:47.819
You're staring, dumbass.

09:47.821 --> 09:50.288
I wasn't staring.

09:50.290 --> 09:51.723
No, whatever you say,
Brokeback Rain Man.

09:51.725 --> 09:52.557
Vince!
What?

09:52.559 --> 09:54.259
Stop.
Hey, it's cool.

09:54.261 --> 09:56.194
I'm... I'm all secure
in my shit.

09:56.196 --> 09:58.129
Like, I don't want you to think
that I'm hatin' on

09:58.131 --> 09:59.664
the goofy bitch, I just...

09:59.666 --> 10:01.900
I'm totally into the ladies,
so I gotta be like,

10:01.902 --> 10:05.303
"Yo, you know, keep the homo
party on that side of the...

10:05.305 --> 10:07.305
"the lobby, 'cause
I only bang chicks."

10:07.307 --> 10:08.840
You know what I mean?

10:08.842 --> 10:10.542
Look, it's okay,
don't feel bad about yourself.

10:10.544 --> 10:12.410
I got an appeal.
It's an it-factor.

10:12.412 --> 10:13.612
I wasn't staring.

10:13.614 --> 10:15.013
Does this normally
work for you?

10:15.015 --> 10:17.515
What?
When you talk.

10:21.287 --> 10:22.754
Dramatic tension.

10:25.625 --> 10:26.491
Wow.

10:26.493 --> 10:28.860
I wasn't staring at Vince.

10:30.663 --> 10:34.032
Umm... I'm gonna go
set up before we open.

10:34.034 --> 10:36.034
Well, w... I wasn't staring.

10:36.036 --> 10:38.570
I wasn't.

10:38.572 --> 10:41.640
<i>- Even for the most dedicated
- Cineplex employee,</i>

10:41.642 --> 10:44.542
<i>there are extended
gaps of down-time.</i>

10:44.544 --> 10:46.878
<i>I spend mine watching movies.</i>

10:46.880 --> 10:48.980
<i>Comedy, romance, action,</i>

10:48.982 --> 10:53.318
<i>whatever it is Tyler Perry
thinks he's doing.</i>

10:53.320 --> 10:57.155
<i>As long as I can just watch.
No judging.</i>

11:12.806 --> 11:16.041
<i>Heaven. Heaven.</i>

11:16.043 --> 11:17.043
<i>What...</i>

11:27.186 --> 11:28.753
- Theatre 1 to your left.
- Heaven.

11:34.961 --> 11:36.795
Theatre 2. Heaven.

11:39.499 --> 11:43.068
Theatre 8 to your right. Hell.

12:13.599 --> 12:16.034
Hello?

12:16.036 --> 12:18.069
What do you want?

12:36.156 --> 12:38.423
Good day at work?

12:38.425 --> 12:40.291
Fine. It was fine.

12:40.293 --> 12:41.526
I made eggs.

12:41.528 --> 12:43.528
I'm... I'm not... I'm not...

12:43.530 --> 12:45.396
Are you sick?
No.

12:45.398 --> 12:47.432
Oh, Walt, you don't
look good.

12:47.434 --> 12:48.767
Did you catch something?

12:48.769 --> 12:50.235
I'm fine.

12:50.237 --> 12:51.736
I told you to get a flu shot.

12:51.738 --> 12:53.638
You're working at
that movie theatre,

12:53.640 --> 12:55.974
with all those people
with butter

12:55.976 --> 12:58.309
and bathroom doorknob
feces on their hands.

12:58.311 --> 13:00.345
I'll get the thermometer.

14:54.361 --> 14:55.760
<i>Heaven, heaven.</i>

14:57.162 --> 14:57.996
Listen, man, I don't
know what's wrong...

14:57.998 --> 14:59.264
<i>Hell.</i>

14:59.266 --> 15:00.706
But I need it today,
not tomorrow.

15:07.173 --> 15:09.574
Heaven. Heaven.

15:09.576 --> 15:11.709
Heav...

15:15.081 --> 15:16.614
Heaven.

15:16.616 --> 15:18.549
Heav...

15:18.551 --> 15:20.718
Hell. Heaven.

15:33.999 --> 15:36.434
Theatre 3 to your left. Heaven.

15:40.606 --> 15:44.809
Theatre 2 to your right.
Polo heaven, tank-top hell.

15:44.811 --> 15:46.911
Anybody say he'd be your
Prince Charming?

15:46.913 --> 15:49.647
Do you think or you just
completely...

15:49.649 --> 15:54.085
Uhh, Theatre 4 right...
uhh, to your right. Hell.

15:58.058 --> 15:59.557
Hello?

15:59.559 --> 16:01.759
Come on, man,
I'll miss my movie.
Oh, no, no, no, no.

16:01.761 --> 16:04.395
Where are you going,
ticket guy?

16:04.397 --> 16:07.799
Just make the judgement, kid.

16:07.801 --> 16:09.367
This is not...
Yes or no,

16:09.369 --> 16:11.769
up or down, heaven or hell,
I really don't care,

16:11.771 --> 16:13.771
but I can't be here
any longer.

16:13.773 --> 16:16.174
You're not...
you're not even...

16:16.176 --> 16:18.910
I know who you are.

16:18.912 --> 16:20.445
This isn't...
This isn't...

16:20.447 --> 16:22.180
Do your job.

16:22.182 --> 16:23.781
- I can't get a reading...
- Can I get a new ticket guy?

16:23.783 --> 16:25.116
Mine's broken.

16:25.118 --> 16:27.852
Do... your... job.

16:48.140 --> 16:50.108
Must be nice.

16:50.110 --> 16:53.311
If I had a direct line like you,
I wouldn't have to do this.

16:53.313 --> 16:54.712
Do what? Who are you?

16:54.714 --> 16:55.913
I'm Greg.

16:55.915 --> 16:57.248
Greg?

16:57.250 --> 17:00.885
Yeah. Gregory Douglas Tomlinson,

17:00.887 --> 17:03.087
if that helps with
the paperwork.

17:03.089 --> 17:06.557
How do you...
Hmm? How do I what?

17:08.359 --> 17:10.161
Know who I am. No one knows.

17:11.663 --> 17:13.196
No one living, at least.

17:13.199 --> 17:15.165
Boo.

17:15.167 --> 17:16.968
It's a stupid joke.
It's... I just...

17:16.970 --> 17:20.171
I've been waiting a long time
to try that out, so...

17:20.173 --> 17:21.606
You're dead.

17:21.608 --> 17:23.141
My lack of colour
give me away?

17:23.143 --> 17:24.976
That's why I couldn't
get a read.

17:24.978 --> 17:27.310
So what's the plan?
How did you find me?

17:27.313 --> 17:29.080
I'm dead, Walter.

17:29.082 --> 17:30.448
I'm dead and I'm talking
to you.

17:30.450 --> 17:31.582
I judge the living.

17:31.584 --> 17:32.584
You judge everyone.

17:32.585 --> 17:34.118
Everyone living!

17:38.123 --> 17:40.491
So I'm...

17:40.493 --> 17:41.692
I'm stuck here like this?

17:41.694 --> 17:44.195
I don't know! I... I don't...

17:45.464 --> 17:47.298
Well, I can't!

17:53.405 --> 17:54.572
Living, dead,

17:54.574 --> 17:57.275
what's the difference?

17:57.277 --> 17:58.743
I told you, I can't
get a read...

17:58.745 --> 18:00.578
A read, a read,
right, whatever.

18:00.580 --> 18:02.580
Uhh, make a guess.

18:02.582 --> 18:04.315
I honestly don't care
where you send me,

18:04.317 --> 18:05.683
just get me outta here.

18:05.685 --> 18:07.685
Flip a goddamn coin!

18:14.726 --> 18:15.960
It doesn't work that way.

18:15.962 --> 18:16.761
Why not?

18:16.763 --> 18:18.162
Because I have to know.

18:19.231 --> 18:20.231
Who cares?

18:20.233 --> 18:22.300
He does.

18:22.302 --> 18:24.235
I have to be right,
that's how it works.

18:24.237 --> 18:25.536
And how does that happen

18:25.538 --> 18:28.673
with normal people
who aren't, you know, dead?

18:28.675 --> 18:30.608
I just see them and I know.

18:30.610 --> 18:32.110
You do all this
on a fuckin' hunch?

18:32.112 --> 18:33.945
I wouldn't expect you to
understand how I work.

18:33.947 --> 18:35.746
There's certain... mysteries
that can't be explained.

18:35.748 --> 18:37.415
Mysterious ways, right.

18:37.417 --> 18:39.884
Godspeak for bullshit.

18:44.390 --> 18:48.126
Can't feel anything.

18:48.128 --> 18:50.061
You have any idea
what that's like?

18:52.798 --> 18:53.931
I'm sorry, but I...

18:53.933 --> 18:55.166
I still can't help you.

18:55.168 --> 18:56.968
What's the harm
in trying, Walter?

18:56.970 --> 18:58.369
I have work to do,
and anything that keeps me

18:58.371 --> 19:00.638
from doing that work
is harmful, so please...

19:02.441 --> 19:05.176
Go away.

19:14.721 --> 19:16.187
Okay, I know I promised
not to talk about it...

19:16.189 --> 19:19.157
I'm fine.
You don't look fine.

19:19.159 --> 19:20.925
I told you we're
not talking about it.

19:20.927 --> 19:23.628
Well, you have kind of
a plague-y look.

19:23.630 --> 19:24.762
Plague-y?

19:24.764 --> 19:26.330
Well, a pre-plague-y look,

19:26.332 --> 19:28.132
but that's how it starts.
I don't have the plague.

19:28.134 --> 19:31.302
Ohh, The plague.
As if there's only one.

19:31.304 --> 19:32.970
Goodnight, Mom.

19:32.972 --> 19:35.406
Okay, okay, okay.
This time I promise:

19:35.408 --> 19:37.208
we will not talk about it.

19:37.210 --> 19:39.143
You won't keep that promise.
How do you know?

19:39.145 --> 19:41.078
Because you've broken it five
times since we started eating.

19:41.080 --> 19:43.147
Well, then tell me!
Tell you what?

19:43.149 --> 19:44.448
Whatever it is!

19:47.319 --> 19:48.586
You're gay.

19:48.588 --> 19:50.421
What?

19:50.423 --> 19:51.423
Aren't you?

19:51.424 --> 19:52.424
I'm not gay.

19:52.425 --> 19:53.624
It's okay if you are.

19:53.626 --> 19:55.092
But I'm not.

19:56.996 --> 19:58.196
Well, you're something.

19:58.198 --> 19:59.198
Something not gay!

20:01.467 --> 20:03.701
The book said you'd say that.

20:03.703 --> 20:05.436
And the book about
having a depressed son

20:05.438 --> 20:07.705
said I would deny being
depressed if confronted,

20:07.707 --> 20:10.074
and so did the one about
having an alcoholic son,

20:10.076 --> 20:13.444
and a cutter, and a
crystal meth addict, and...
Hey.

20:13.446 --> 20:17.148
I mean, it makes
the most sense.

20:17.150 --> 20:22.086
And I want you to know that
I am totally okay with it.

20:23.488 --> 20:24.889
Goodnight, Mom.

20:29.428 --> 20:31.062
Walt!

20:31.064 --> 20:34.065
I'm not sick, I'm not gay
and I'm not hungry.

20:44.243 --> 20:47.044
Whatever's going on with you,
you have to talk about it.

20:47.046 --> 20:50.047
If not with me,
then with somebody.

20:50.049 --> 20:52.750
There must be good
therapists out there.

20:52.752 --> 20:55.987
We can find one.

20:55.989 --> 20:57.788
Walt?

20:57.790 --> 20:58.790
Walt!

20:58.791 --> 21:00.191
I'm not dead, Mom.

21:01.660 --> 21:03.127
Just checking.

21:51.743 --> 21:53.844
Karen?

21:53.846 --> 21:55.179
Karen Benjamin?

21:55.181 --> 21:56.080
No.

21:56.082 --> 21:57.448
Oh, my Christ, is that you?

21:57.450 --> 22:00.518
I haven't seen you in so...
Honey, hug!

22:00.520 --> 22:03.688
Oh...
Oh, yeah, we're doin' it!

22:03.690 --> 22:05.823
How are you?
I'm great.

22:05.825 --> 22:07.325
I gotta tell you,

22:07.327 --> 22:10.628
that office was never
the same after you left, mmm-mm.

22:10.630 --> 22:11.996
Oh...
Really.

22:11.998 --> 22:13.497
What have you been doing?

22:13.499 --> 22:14.832
How's little Walter?

22:14.834 --> 22:16.200
Oh, I guess he's not
so little anymore.

22:16.202 --> 22:17.868
Gotta be in college
by now, right?

22:17.870 --> 22:20.705
Yeah, college and...
girlfriend.

22:20.707 --> 22:22.139
I mean, he's great.

22:22.141 --> 22:23.841
We're... we're... we're great.

22:23.843 --> 22:25.242
Oh, that's great!

22:26.478 --> 22:28.479
Umm...

22:28.481 --> 22:30.114
Wow!

22:30.116 --> 22:32.676
Oh, well, you know,
we ran out of eggs.

23:32.779 --> 23:34.545
Hey, Walter.

23:34.547 --> 23:36.480
You want some popcorn?

23:36.482 --> 23:38.048
I made it just for you.

23:38.050 --> 23:40.818
Special.
With extra butter...

23:40.820 --> 23:42.920
and bathroom doorknob feces.

23:45.324 --> 23:49.160
Let me know how many eggs
you want for breakfast, Walt.

23:50.962 --> 23:52.663
Wally?

23:52.665 --> 23:55.566
Walter!

23:55.568 --> 23:56.967
Walter.

24:00.106 --> 24:02.473
Walter...

24:03.809 --> 24:06.444
