He used to take me here a lot.

41:35.794 --> 41:37.160
Who?
Jim.

41:37.162 --> 41:38.828
Who's Jim?
Even after he got sick.

41:38.830 --> 41:40.897
"A nice escape from reality,"
he called it.

41:40.899 --> 41:42.432
Walter...
So now I work here.

41:42.434 --> 41:44.501
But instead of doing
my cineplex duties,

41:44.503 --> 41:45.969
I'm the trash collector/
trash emptier,

41:45.971 --> 41:47.237
which is the punishment
for being late,

41:47.239 --> 41:48.439
which I only am
because of you,

41:48.440 --> 41:49.839
which... which I don't
even think

41:49.841 --> 41:52.281
you've properly acknowledged.
You miss him?

41:55.246 --> 41:57.180
- They don't miss me.
- I mean, you know.

41:57.182 --> 41:58.948
I have to go back to work.

41:58.950 --> 42:00.783
You know her, don't ya?

42:00.785 --> 42:03.019
Who?
Allie.

42:03.021 --> 42:04.754
The way you looked at her,
at the church.

42:04.756 --> 42:06.222
I need to get back inside...
How do you know her?

42:06.224 --> 42:07.957
Just please leave me alone.

42:07.959 --> 42:10.493
I'm not gonna watch her walk
down that aisle, Walter.

42:10.495 --> 42:13.329
It has to be now!
Do your job!

42:33.918 --> 42:35.218
No!

42:35.220 --> 42:37.220
Church? Really?

42:37.222 --> 42:38.688
I know we talked about this.

42:38.690 --> 42:41.624
You let Greg the ghost take you
to a house of worship?!

42:41.626 --> 42:42.792
You did that!

42:42.794 --> 42:44.027
Can I just explain...

42:44.029 --> 42:46.362
Hold on, I've gotta
get another lap in

42:46.364 --> 42:48.331
before I listen to this.

42:48.333 --> 42:50.800
Oh, my...

42:50.802 --> 42:52.402
Alright.

42:57.875 --> 42:58.942
Go.
I just thought that...

42:58.944 --> 42:59.976
It's crazy.

42:59.978 --> 43:01.377
What?

43:01.379 --> 43:02.478
It doesn't matter
what you're about to say

43:02.480 --> 43:04.047
if what you're about to say is

43:04.049 --> 43:05.548
you went to church
with a dead guy.

43:05.550 --> 43:07.483
Who we both had agreed
was not an actual dead guy,

43:07.485 --> 43:10.520
but the kind of dead guy
only crazy people see!

43:10.522 --> 43:11.988
But, you don't...
Crazy!

43:11.990 --> 43:13.923
And I will be completely
honest with you.

43:13.925 --> 43:16.626
You're lookin' a bit off
at the moment.
Off?

43:16.628 --> 43:19.729
Not that you were ever
a picture of "on." No...

43:19.731 --> 43:22.031
Should I leave?
Yes.

43:22.033 --> 43:23.666
Really?

43:23.668 --> 43:26.903
You didn't have an appointment.
You said I could come in!

43:26.905 --> 43:28.137
Why did you come here?

43:28.139 --> 43:29.672
Because I think that this
is an emergency.

43:29.674 --> 43:32.175
No, no, I mean, why did you
come here initially?

43:32.177 --> 43:34.911
I... came here to...

43:34.913 --> 43:36.012
To?

43:36.014 --> 43:37.180
Stop seeing the...

43:37.182 --> 43:38.314
To stop seeing
Greg the ghost,

43:38.316 --> 43:39.882
that's why you came here.

43:39.884 --> 43:42.585
You knew enough to know that
seeing dead people was crazy.

43:42.587 --> 43:43.419
So why,

43:43.421 --> 43:46.122
Walter Gary Benjamin,

43:46.124 --> 43:48.024
are you now going on
dates with him?!

43:48.026 --> 43:49.425
He's very persistant!

43:52.096 --> 43:53.396
Leave.
What?

43:53.398 --> 43:54.998
Seriously, you gotta go.

43:55.000 --> 43:56.666
But... but... I'm trying...
Crazy.

43:56.668 --> 43:58.701
He... you don't understand.
He seems real.

43:58.703 --> 44:00.970
Crazy.
He's got a family,
and I know they're real.

44:00.972 --> 44:02.605
Straight-up batshit.

44:02.607 --> 44:05.308
I'm sorry, Walter, but that's
my professional opinion;

44:05.310 --> 44:07.677
you're beyond fixing. Goodbye.

44:14.685 --> 44:17.153
You know Greg
ain't the problem, right?

44:19.690 --> 44:21.524
I just came here because
I just... I just need...

44:21.526 --> 44:23.092
I know why you think
you came here,

44:23.094 --> 44:24.560
but that doesn't help me,

44:24.562 --> 44:26.129
and I doubt it's doing
much for you either.

44:26.131 --> 44:28.064
Aren't you supposed to ask me
questions about stuff?

44:28.066 --> 44:29.932
Isn't that how this works?

44:29.934 --> 44:31.734
It's a pretty popular
approach, yeah.

44:31.736 --> 44:34.203
What do you think you should
be asking me about?

44:34.205 --> 44:36.339
I got these pages and pages
of notes here,

44:36.341 --> 44:39.709
mostly stuff about Greg.
And try as I might,

44:39.711 --> 44:41.911
with my undeniable
talent and insight,

44:41.913 --> 44:45.448
I can't seem to come up with a
single worthwhile question

44:45.450 --> 44:47.417
out of any of this.

44:50.254 --> 44:52.622
But...

44:52.624 --> 44:55.625
There is one question
we touched on briefly

44:55.627 --> 44:58.628
that I'm thinking might
merit a second look.

45:06.403 --> 45:07.770
Who's Jim?

45:11.910 --> 45:16.112
I love the movies, Dad...

45:20.151 --> 45:21.617
Come on, Walter.

45:36.534 --> 45:38.334
<i>No one is coming.</i>

45:38.336 --> 45:42.271
<i>And we're all gonna starve
to death if we stay up here.</i>

45:42.273 --> 45:44.107
<i>What are you saying?</i>

45:46.010 --> 45:48.911
<i>I'm saying that those things
are still in the house,</i>

45:48.913 --> 45:50.580
<i>and if we stay up here</i>

45:50.582 --> 45:54.217
<i>with no food or no water,
we're all gonna die.</i>

45:54.219 --> 45:55.818
<i>First David.</i>

45:58.355 --> 46:02.792
<i>Then Mersp, Centreller.</i>

46:02.794 --> 46:04.727
<i>And then Teller.</i>

46:04.729 --> 46:07.497
<i>There is no search
and rescue.</i>

46:09.967 --> 46:12.869
<i>We're gonna have to leave.</i>

46:12.871 --> 46:15.872
<i>First, someone's gonna have
to go get it,</i>

46:15.874 --> 46:17.106
<i>and bring it around
the other side of...</i>

46:17.108 --> 46:19.208
Hey, Wally.

46:20.979 --> 46:25.081
Uhh... how'd you know
it was me?

46:25.083 --> 46:26.415
<i>What about me?</i>

46:26.417 --> 46:29.552
You're always sort of here,
aren't you?

46:29.554 --> 46:30.753
<i>Hopefully they'll stay</i>

46:30.755 --> 46:32.622
<i>where I can see really well.</i>

46:32.624 --> 46:36.325
I guess I love movies.

46:36.327 --> 46:40.897
I know. I'm sure
you do, but...

46:40.899 --> 46:44.167
it's different
for you, isn't it?

46:44.169 --> 46:47.203
<i>I don't know, Taylor,
what if they...</i>

46:47.205 --> 46:49.071
Everything sort of is.

46:49.073 --> 46:52.975
<i>You know what happens</i>
<i>if we stay up here.</i>
I'm sorry.

46:52.977 --> 46:54.977
I'm sorry, I'm just...

46:57.447 --> 47:00.383
The crazy thing is,
I really like this movie.

47:04.555 --> 47:07.824
Well, then why are
you crying?

47:07.826 --> 47:09.525
<i>These guys are gonna
be chasing you,</i>

47:09.527 --> 47:11.928
<i>so you'll have
to punch the car...</i>

47:11.930 --> 47:13.963
I don't know.

47:18.269 --> 47:21.003
We're all broken, Wally.

47:26.109 --> 47:27.543
But maybe that's okay.

47:27.545 --> 47:28.678
<i>You got it?</i>

47:28.680 --> 47:30.279
<i>I got it.</i>

47:30.281 --> 47:32.615
<i>Okay, I'm going.</i>

48:42.419 --> 48:44.120
Please go away.

48:49.059 --> 48:50.960
Whatcha prayin' for?

48:50.962 --> 48:52.595
The girl?
It's the girl, right?

48:52.597 --> 48:55.464
Askin' Daddy to pull
a few strings? I like it.

48:55.466 --> 48:58.067
I mean, if the Son of God can't
get the girl of his dreams,

48:58.069 --> 49:01.737
really, what chance does
true love have in this world?

49:03.073 --> 49:04.540
Why are you doing this?

49:04.542 --> 49:09.545
Allie will be someone else's
wife in less than an hour.

49:09.547 --> 49:11.514
Please.
I can't help you.

49:11.516 --> 49:13.115
What if I told you everything?

49:13.117 --> 49:14.951
What?

49:16.954 --> 49:18.688
Like everything.

49:18.690 --> 49:21.657
The stuff that you normally
see when you...

49:21.659 --> 49:23.526
look into someone's
soul or whatever.

49:23.528 --> 49:25.962
I'll just lay it out there.

49:25.964 --> 49:27.797
It doesn't work that way,
and even if it did,

49:27.799 --> 49:29.065
how would I know you were
telling me the truth?

49:29.067 --> 49:30.566
You don't even
have the instincts

49:30.568 --> 49:32.001
to tell if a man's
lying or not?

49:32.003 --> 49:33.235
Ask me anything!

49:33.237 --> 49:34.570
You think I'm bullshitting you
in any way,

49:34.572 --> 49:36.339
I will leave you
alone forever.

49:36.341 --> 49:38.341
I can't really get
into the logistics...
She was gonna leave me.

49:38.343 --> 49:40.710
Why are you telling me this?

49:42.279 --> 49:46.549
You might understand this...
unrequited pining thing

49:46.551 --> 49:51.053
or whatever you're doing
with Popcorn Girl, but, uhh...

49:51.055 --> 49:55.558
to actually have the girl,
to have her love you...

49:55.560 --> 49:59.362
like, start a family together...

49:59.364 --> 50:01.864
to know someone in such a
perfect way, like completely,

50:01.866 --> 50:04.700
that's the best, man.

50:04.702 --> 50:07.169
That's the best. I had that.

50:09.706 --> 50:11.474
So you think I'm
afraid of Hell?

50:11.476 --> 50:14.577
That's Hell. Worse than Hell.
Having that, losing it.

50:14.579 --> 50:18.748
Don't need you or God
or anyone else

50:18.750 --> 50:20.983
to explain that to me.

50:23.755 --> 50:25.921
So what do you say, Walter?

50:25.923 --> 50:28.190
Walter?

50:28.192 --> 50:30.659
Deal with me, you chicken-shit
little bitch...

50:30.661 --> 50:32.828
How'd you die?

50:35.999 --> 50:38.534
What am I supposed...
How did you die?

50:50.013 --> 50:52.615
I mean...

50:52.617 --> 50:54.550
she was my life.

51:07.264 --> 51:10.232
I answer your question,
and you run off.

51:10.234 --> 51:11.567
Poor form, Son of God.

51:11.569 --> 51:13.636
Poor form. What are you doing?

51:13.638 --> 51:15.237
We have to go.

51:15.239 --> 51:16.338
Go where?

51:16.340 --> 51:17.540
Another field trip.

51:32.556 --> 51:34.090
No.

51:34.092 --> 51:35.291
You think it started
already?

51:35.293 --> 51:36.525
What does it matter?

51:36.527 --> 51:38.594
It's not like you're
invited.

51:38.596 --> 51:39.795
Whoa, hey, Walter!

51:39.797 --> 51:41.263
I need to talk to her!
Whoa!

51:41.265 --> 51:42.865
Don't do this, man!

51:42.867 --> 51:45.668
You can't just show up
at her wedding.

51:45.670 --> 51:48.370
Hey, hey, what's the plan here?

51:52.810 --> 51:54.543
Excuse me.
...honourable estate.

51:54.545 --> 51:56.212
Excuse me!
Made by God in Paradise,

51:56.214 --> 51:57.680
into its holy...

51:57.682 --> 51:58.682
Excuse me!

51:59.750 --> 52:01.250
Uhh... sorry, sorry.

52:01.252 --> 52:02.451
I'm sorry to interrupt.

52:02.453 --> 52:04.620
Son, I'm sorry, this is
a private ceremony.

52:04.622 --> 52:06.455
I need to talk to the...
I'm gonna have to ask you
to leave right now.

52:06.457 --> 52:08.824
My name is Walter Gary Benjamin,
I need to talk to the bride!

52:08.826 --> 52:10.392
Really?

52:10.394 --> 52:11.827
Wait!

52:13.498 --> 52:15.865
It's okay, I know him.

52:37.120 --> 52:39.555
Uhh, Allie...

52:39.557 --> 52:44.160
Can you give us a minute?
Please?

52:44.162 --> 52:47.463
Just trust me, I...

52:47.465 --> 52:48.764
You yell if you need me.

52:48.766 --> 52:50.166
I will.

52:54.771 --> 52:58.340
I gotta say, your timing
could use some work.

52:58.342 --> 53:01.076
Do you know why I'm here?

53:04.181 --> 53:05.381
Do you?

53:09.886 --> 53:12.154
You were at the rehearsal too,
weren't you?

53:12.156 --> 53:16.959
I couldn't quite place
you then, but...

53:20.030 --> 53:22.698
You look just like him.

53:33.411 --> 53:34.810
Are you okay?

53:36.247 --> 53:37.646
No.

53:40.484 --> 53:43.252
No, I'm not.

53:43.254 --> 53:44.334
Walter.

53:53.663 --> 53:54.863
Walter?

54:24.661 --> 54:27.129
Oh, this smells so good.

54:27.131 --> 54:28.764
Well, you probably won't be able
to keep much down

54:28.766 --> 54:30.399
once you start chemo.

54:30.401 --> 54:33.168
I figured you should have a shot
at some real food beforehand.

54:34.070 --> 54:37.373
Last meal, so to speak.

54:37.375 --> 54:38.874
Don't say that.

54:43.714 --> 54:47.916
Is it bad... that I love you?

54:55.825 --> 54:58.160
I'm sorry, I shouldn't...
No, no, no, no.

55:00.964 --> 55:02.898
It's okay.

55:11.541 --> 55:15.077
<i>Doctor Forrest, dial 118,
please.</i>

55:15.079 --> 55:18.080
<i>Doctor Forrest,
please dial 1-1-8.</i>

55:25.589 --> 55:27.790
Mom?

55:27.792 --> 55:30.125
Mom? Mom! Mom!

55:36.767 --> 55:39.835
Stop it, stop it.
Stop it! Stop!

55:39.837 --> 55:42.438
Stop!

55:42.440 --> 55:44.573
No, stop, stop!
Walter?

55:44.575 --> 55:47.042
Wal... hey, Walter, honey,
take a deep breath.

55:47.044 --> 55:49.845
Are you okay?
I'm calling 911.
No, Darren, he's...

55:49.847 --> 55:51.146
This is crazy!

55:51.148 --> 55:52.214
Walter, it's okay, honey.
No, no, no...

55:52.216 --> 55:53.515
Okay, look, take a deep breath

55:53.517 --> 55:55.050
and come sit down
for a moment, okay?

55:55.052 --> 55:56.318
She is a nurse, listen to her!
Okay, Darren...

55:56.320 --> 55:57.320
I should go.

55:57.321 --> 55:59.788
I loved him!

55:59.790 --> 56:01.190
If that matters.

56:03.660 --> 56:05.694
So did I.

56:05.696 --> 56:07.663
And it doesn't.

56:19.075 --> 56:20.109
Hey!

56:27.951 --> 56:29.852
Told you it was a bad idea.

56:29.854 --> 56:31.453
Why didn't you say anything?

56:31.455 --> 56:35.057
Look, man, I had my own shit
to figure out here.

56:35.059 --> 56:36.492
How was I supposed
to know about...

56:36.494 --> 56:38.427
Wait, you knew about Jim
and Allie this whole time?

56:38.429 --> 56:42.831
Look, I think maybe we should,
uhh, calm down a bit, before...

56:42.833 --> 56:45.200
Answer the question.

56:45.202 --> 56:47.169
Of course I fuckin' knew.

56:47.171 --> 56:48.971
You gonna try
and tell me you didn't?

56:50.874 --> 56:51.974
What?

56:51.976 --> 56:54.443
I mean, really.

56:54.445 --> 56:56.178
How long do we
keep doing this?

56:56.180 --> 56:57.446
I didn't even know
that she existed

56:57.448 --> 56:58.547
until you brought me
over here yourself.

56:58.549 --> 57:01.350
We both know nothing happened
that you didn't already know.

57:01.352 --> 57:03.952
No, no, no. Everything made
sense until you showed up.

57:03.954 --> 57:05.287
Everything made sense

57:05.289 --> 57:06.922
until you started
thinkin' about shit.

57:06.924 --> 57:07.924
No, no-no, no-no.

57:07.925 --> 57:09.558
Don't, don't.

57:11.594 --> 57:12.895
Don't!

57:12.897 --> 57:14.496
Hey, man,
why am I still here?

57:14.498 --> 57:15.564
Leave me alone!

57:15.566 --> 57:17.099
If you wanted me
to leave you alone,

57:17.101 --> 57:20.102
you would have done your job!
But maybe,

57:20.104 --> 57:22.584
it's not really
your job, after all.

57:24.674 --> 57:26.074
How do you know?

57:31.648 --> 57:32.748
Come on.

57:32.750 --> 57:35.150
Really? We're doing that?

57:35.152 --> 57:36.718
Alright.
Leave me alone!

57:36.720 --> 57:38.020
Okay.

57:38.022 --> 57:41.023
You know, I did a
little cross-country

57:41.025 --> 57:43.091
in high school.

57:43.093 --> 57:44.460
Plus I'm dead!

57:44.462 --> 57:47.496
So I don't have to,
you know, breathe!

57:47.498 --> 57:49.932
You might wanna re-think the
"outrunning me" plan!

57:57.508 --> 57:59.875
Leave me alone!

58:56.467 --> 58:58.267
That worked out well for ya.

58:59.936 --> 59:01.203
Get outta here.

59:10.980 --> 59:13.615
You know, I forgave her.
Allie.

59:13.617 --> 59:14.850
A long time ago, actually.

59:14.852 --> 59:16.785
That's the funny thing
about bein' dead:

59:16.787 --> 59:20.455
you don't really dwell on the
things that you'd expect to.

59:20.457 --> 59:24.626
See, the only thing that
really sticks with you,

59:24.628 --> 59:27.729
haunts you even,

59:27.731 --> 59:30.399
is the overwhelming feeling
that you were alive,

59:30.401 --> 59:34.469
you fucking existed,
and you wasted it.

59:36.306 --> 59:40.609
Ten years is
a long time to waste.

59:45.181 --> 59:46.782
You ready?

59:50.019 --> 59:51.753
You tell me.

01:02:57.006 --> 01:02:58.073
Walt?

01:02:58.075 --> 01:02:59.075
Mom.

01:02:59.076 --> 01:03:01.343
I heard...

01:03:06.082 --> 01:03:07.649
I sent Jim to Hell.

01:03:10.119 --> 01:03:12.020
What?

01:03:12.022 --> 01:03:15.056
I sent Jim to Hell
right after he died,

01:03:15.058 --> 01:03:17.726
and there's nothing
I can do about it now.

01:03:19.796 --> 01:03:20.862
Are you feeling okay?

01:03:20.864 --> 01:03:22.330
Would you like me
to make you some eggs?

01:03:22.332 --> 01:03:23.865
I'm not hungry.

01:03:27.170 --> 01:03:28.770
Maybe I should make up a batch,

01:03:28.772 --> 01:03:31.206
just in case your body is so
calorie-deprived you're...

01:03:31.208 --> 01:03:33.208
starting to feed
on your organs.

01:03:33.210 --> 01:03:34.876
I'm not hungry, Mom.

01:03:34.878 --> 01:03:36.244
Now see, that's the thing
about the more advanced

01:03:36.246 --> 01:03:37.246
stages of starvation...

01:03:37.247 --> 01:03:39.848
I'm not fucking hungry!

01:03:46.656 --> 01:03:49.357
I sent him to Hell.
Don't you want to know why?

01:03:51.360 --> 01:03:53.128
You're not making any sense.

01:03:53.130 --> 01:03:55.430
We never talk about it,
but you knew, didn't you?

01:03:59.069 --> 01:04:01.670
I think you need
some sleep...

01:04:01.672 --> 01:04:04.673
He broke your heart.
That's what you need.

01:04:04.675 --> 01:04:07.943
Walt...
He broke your heart,
and I sent him to Hell for it.

01:04:07.945 --> 01:04:12.113
Walt...
You used to be different.
You used to be happy.

01:04:12.115 --> 01:04:14.382
You weren't always like...

01:04:14.384 --> 01:04:16.618
Like what?
Like this!

01:04:19.522 --> 01:04:20.789
Your father was a good man!

01:04:20.791 --> 01:04:23.058
And her husband...
that woman had a husband,

01:04:23.060 --> 01:04:24.559
in case you didn't know that,

01:04:24.561 --> 01:04:26.928
her husband found out,
and he killed himself,
Walt...

01:04:26.930 --> 01:04:28.797
because Jim and Allie cared
more about themselves

01:04:28.799 --> 01:04:30.765
than they ever did
about anybody else!

01:04:30.767 --> 01:04:33.301
Your father made a mistake!

01:04:33.303 --> 01:04:35.170
Now, you can't
blame him for that!

01:04:35.172 --> 01:04:37.572
Jim wasn't my father.

01:04:37.574 --> 01:04:42.344
Will you stop it?
You stop it, right now!

01:04:42.346 --> 01:04:44.479
He wasn't perfect!

01:04:44.481 --> 01:04:47.449
But he loved us, and you.

01:04:47.451 --> 01:04:49.784
He loved you more
than anything!

01:04:49.786 --> 01:04:51.586
More than Allie?

01:04:51.588 --> 01:04:53.121
That's enough!

01:04:58.461 --> 01:05:01.296
Do you wanna know what
broke my heart, Walt?

01:05:01.298 --> 01:05:02.931
Really?

01:05:02.933 --> 01:05:05.901
Because it wasn't just him
messing around with some nurse,

01:05:05.903 --> 01:05:08.737
right after he found out
he was dying.

01:05:08.739 --> 01:05:12.607
Yeah, that hurt.
And I let him know.

01:05:12.609 --> 01:05:17.178
But it couldn't erase
a lifetime with him.

01:05:17.180 --> 01:05:19.214
Not even close!

01:05:19.216 --> 01:05:20.615
And it wasn't even him dying.

01:05:20.617 --> 01:05:24.219
I had the strength to get us
through losing him.

01:05:24.221 --> 01:05:27.722
And you're right,
I was different then.

01:05:27.724 --> 01:05:30.025
I was strong, Walt!

01:05:30.027 --> 01:05:32.494
I was strong enough
to watch him die!

01:05:32.496 --> 01:05:35.697
But it wasn't losing him
that broke me!

01:05:35.699 --> 01:05:38.767
It was losing you
that killed me.

01:05:43.707 --> 01:05:47.242
Now there's eggs on the wall,
and on the floor,

01:05:47.244 --> 01:05:48.843
if you're hungry.

01:06:38.462 --> 01:06:41.896
Hell, hell.

01:06:41.898 --> 01:06:43.898
Hell.

01:06:45.301 --> 01:06:46.301
Hell.

01:06:46.303 --> 01:06:50.472
Hell, hell, hell. Hell.

01:07:04.387 --> 01:07:07.555
Theatre 6 down the hall
to your right. Hell.

01:07:10.126 --> 01:07:11.593
Theatre 1, down the hall
to your left.

01:07:11.595 --> 01:07:12.994
Hell.

01:07:15.598 --> 01:07:18.133
Theatre 6, hell.

01:07:18.135 --> 01:07:20.068
Hell. Hell.

01:07:21.604 --> 01:07:22.871
You're all going to hell!

01:07:22.873 --> 01:07:25.507
- What?
- All of you.

01:07:28.245 --> 01:07:30.945
Okay.

01:07:59.308 --> 01:08:00.875
You look like shit.

01:08:00.877 --> 01:08:03.645
Forgive me for stating the
obvious, but it's so obvious

01:08:03.647 --> 01:08:05.780
I felt personally and
professionally obligated

01:08:05.782 --> 01:08:07.482
to say something about it.

01:08:07.484 --> 01:08:09.517
When's the last time
you slept?

01:08:09.519 --> 01:08:10.985
I don't know.

01:08:10.987 --> 01:08:13.721
Ate?

01:08:13.723 --> 01:08:17.125
Eggs.
I think I had eggs.

01:08:17.127 --> 01:08:18.158
When?

01:08:18.161 --> 01:08:20.462
I don't... I don't remember.

01:08:24.133 --> 01:08:25.867
Well, I won't ask
about bathing,

01:08:25.868 --> 01:08:28.736
'cause I think I know
the answer to that one.

01:08:28.738 --> 01:08:31.171
How's Greg?

01:08:33.609 --> 01:08:36.211
You know, your ghost friend.

01:08:36.212 --> 01:08:38.580
I thought you didn't
wanna talk about Greg.

01:08:38.582 --> 01:08:39.781
I don't, but you do, right?

01:08:39.783 --> 01:08:42.082
Not anymore.

01:08:42.085 --> 01:08:44.519
Well, that's why
we're here, right?

01:08:44.520 --> 01:08:45.920
Your ghost problem?

01:08:47.456 --> 01:08:48.723
I'm not crazy.

01:08:48.725 --> 01:08:50.725
Are you sure?

01:08:52.761 --> 01:08:54.362
I don't...

01:08:56.932 --> 01:08:59.134
I don't know. I... I...

01:09:00.836 --> 01:09:02.537
You're just supposed to...

01:09:02.538 --> 01:09:03.671
What am I supposed to do?

01:09:03.673 --> 01:09:05.640
Just stop. Just stop.

01:09:05.642 --> 01:09:07.175
What am I doing, Walter?
You know!

01:09:07.176 --> 01:09:10.712
You know! You...
you always know what you...

01:09:10.714 --> 01:09:13.148
God, you know exactly what...

01:09:15.151 --> 01:09:19.953
I can't... I can't.
I don't know. I don't know.

01:09:19.956 --> 01:09:21.356
I don't know. I don't know.

01:09:24.126 --> 01:09:25.760
I had control.

01:09:29.966 --> 01:09:33.434
You can sit there,
and you can... and you can

01:09:33.435 --> 01:09:35.303
tell me what's real,
and what's crazy,

01:09:35.305 --> 01:09:37.305
and what's total bullshit
and you can say that

01:09:37.307 --> 01:09:39.140
I'm just some kid who doesn't
know how to function properly

01:09:39.142 --> 01:09:43.478
in the world, you can say all
that. Okay? Fine. Fine.

01:09:43.479 --> 01:09:46.848
But I had control.

01:09:46.850 --> 01:09:48.883
I woke up every day
and I went outside,

01:09:48.885 --> 01:09:51.152
and I did something.

01:09:51.154 --> 01:09:54.189
I did something. I never...
I never took a personal day,

01:09:54.191 --> 01:09:57.458
I never called in sick,
I never made excuses

01:09:57.460 --> 01:09:58.860
for why life is unfair, I...

01:09:58.862 --> 01:10:01.796
I... figured out my place.

01:10:02.898 --> 01:10:06.834
I see so many people
that are just...

01:10:06.836 --> 01:10:10.338
they're just wasting
so much time,

01:10:10.340 --> 01:10:12.774
doing nothing.

01:10:12.776 --> 01:10:15.376
And that's crazy.
That's crazy.

01:10:20.183 --> 01:10:22.917
They're...

01:10:22.919 --> 01:10:26.087
Things can happen. Things can
happen. They can be bad.

01:10:26.089 --> 01:10:27.655
They can be worse than bad.
They... they...

01:10:27.657 --> 01:10:30.158
they can destroy you
if you let them.

01:10:30.160 --> 01:10:33.661
If you even acknowledge them,
they can destroy you,

01:10:33.663 --> 01:10:36.064
so I took control
and I made rules,

01:10:36.066 --> 01:10:37.799
and I followed them
without question,

01:10:37.801 --> 01:10:39.867
and I... and I...

01:10:41.704 --> 01:10:45.173
I thought... I just thought...
I thought that if I did that,

01:10:45.175 --> 01:10:48.076
then nothing...
could tear me apart,

01:10:48.078 --> 01:10:50.778
the way... the way that
cancer did with Jim,

01:10:50.780 --> 01:10:53.214
that life did with my mom.

01:11:08.330 --> 01:11:11.899
Sounds crazy?
Does this sound crazy?

01:11:16.806 --> 01:11:18.506
I know this... I know.

01:11:21.110 --> 01:11:25.013
I know it sounds crazy,
I know it sounds crazy, I...

01:11:30.786 --> 01:11:32.954
I probably am crazy.

01:11:35.891 --> 01:11:37.492
I just...

01:11:37.494 --> 01:11:41.195
I just need you to help me.
I just need you to help me.

01:11:41.197 --> 01:11:44.732
That's what I...
I just need...

01:11:44.734 --> 01:11:46.801
I just need you to help me.

01:11:46.803 --> 01:11:49.337
I need help.

01:11:55.811 --> 01:11:57.178
I'm sorry.

01:12:02.751 --> 01:12:04.585
You know how something
really funny

01:12:04.587 --> 01:12:07.221
just pops into your head
at like the worst times?

01:12:07.223 --> 01:12:09.424
And the more you try
not to laugh,

01:12:09.426 --> 01:12:11.759
the funnier... here I was,
sitting here,

01:12:11.761 --> 01:12:13.861
hoping for something
really good,

01:12:13.863 --> 01:12:16.664
some legit case-study
crazy shit.

01:12:16.666 --> 01:12:21.202
And instead...

01:12:21.204 --> 01:12:22.603
...and this is the funny part,

01:12:22.605 --> 01:12:26.174
the joke I can't help
but laughing at...

01:12:26.176 --> 01:12:28.376
you're not crazy.

01:12:28.378 --> 01:12:30.011
What do you mean?

01:12:30.013 --> 01:12:32.714
You're fine.
This is okay.

01:12:32.716 --> 01:12:34.449
You're not crazy.

01:12:34.451 --> 01:12:37.251
You are not crazy.

01:12:37.253 --> 01:12:40.054
You just forgot to grieve.

01:12:50.065 --> 01:12:51.999
Time's up.

01:13:02.745 --> 01:13:05.046
Hey, Walter...

01:13:05.048 --> 01:13:06.881
I don't mean to put you
on the spot or anything,

01:13:06.883 --> 01:13:08.983
but am I still going to hell?

01:13:11.687 --> 01:13:14.422
I don't know.

01:13:15.657 --> 01:13:18.960
I'll see you next week.

01:17:35.784 --> 01:17:37.284
Mom?

01:17:38.553 --> 01:17:40.321
Mom?

01:18:16.792 --> 01:18:19.593
How'd you sleep?

01:18:19.595 --> 01:18:21.262
Okay.

01:18:21.264 --> 01:18:23.164
I hate not making you anything,

01:18:23.166 --> 01:18:26.734
but, um, I didn't
want to be late.

01:18:26.736 --> 01:18:28.936
Late?

01:18:28.938 --> 01:18:32.707
I, um, have an interview...

01:18:32.709 --> 01:18:34.809
for a job.

01:18:34.811 --> 01:18:36.844
That's great, Mom.

01:18:36.846 --> 01:18:38.279
Yeah.

01:18:38.281 --> 01:18:41.582
Yeah, it is.

01:18:43.285 --> 01:18:45.845
Have a nice day
at work, Walt.

01:18:52.127 --> 01:18:54.328
Thank you.

01:19:55.791 --> 01:19:58.058
<i>- My name is
- Walter Gary Benjamin.</i>

01:19:58.060 --> 01:20:00.694
<i>My friends call me "Wally."</i>

01:20:02.631 --> 01:20:06.734
<i>My mom has always
gone with "Walt."</i>

01:20:06.736 --> 01:20:10.404
<i>And my dad, whenever
I talked to him,</i>

01:20:10.406 --> 01:20:12.139
<i>he'd go with "Walter."</i>

01:20:12.141 --> 01:20:15.342
<i>He's dead, by the way, my dad.</i>

01:20:15.344 --> 01:20:18.445
<i>But I'm not.</i>

01:20:19.748 --> 01:20:22.716
Oh, late again, stupid fuck.
Hey, you keep this up,

01:20:22.718 --> 01:20:24.885
you're going to be the permanent
trash bitch around here.

01:20:24.887 --> 01:20:25.887
Vince?
Yeah?

01:20:25.888 --> 01:20:27.922
Fuck you.

01:20:27.924 --> 01:20:30.925
When you're late, I can't
give Vince the shit work

01:20:30.927 --> 01:20:34.728
and I enjoy giving
Vince the shit work.

